From: kelivo-win7 <dev@kelivo.local> Date: 2026-06-29 Subject: [PATCH 3/9] dart: revert PathCchCombineEx (Win8+) to PathCombine (Win7-compat)  Dart SDK fixed a bug where relative symlinks to directories did not work on Windows (issue <unknown>). The fix used PathCchCombineEx which is only available on Windows 8+.  Revert to PathCombine (Win7-compatible, with a small buffer size limitation of MAX_PATH = 260 chars 鈥?fine for Kelivo's use).  Upstream commit:   https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/b4574904f9cd0d6f7147950c02ee2447569d0be9   "Fix a bug where relative symlinks to directories did not work on Windows"  Files affected:   - runtime/bin/file_win.cc (File::GetType)  Side effect: relative symlink handling on Win7 may regress. Kelivo uses absolute paths for all config and data storage, so this does not affect Kelivo functionality.  === How to generate this patch from engine source === Run in your engine/src/dart directory:   git revert b4574904f9cd0d6f7147950c02ee2447569d0be9 --no-edit   # (If 3.12.1 has the commit)   git format-patch -1 HEAD